        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 2:43PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pratt, or 17 miles northwest of Fayetteville, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Oak Hill, Montgomery, Ansted, Cedar Grove, East Bank, Glasgow,
Smithers, Gauley Bridge, Pratt, Powellton, Hawks Nest State Park,
Handley, Dawes, Swiss, Sharon, and Pond Gap.

This includes West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 72 and 82.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
